Movie: The Discreet Charm of the Bourgeoisie
Review: this was my first Luis Buñuel flick and it honestly rocked. I was not expecting this to be as surreal as it was. there were certain dream sequences that were gripping and boring (ie the lieutenant killing his pseudo-father, the ghost police man?) but other moments were filled with an absurdity and ridiculousness that only made the main 6’s blase, indifferent attitude even more funny. a depressing reminder that for rich people, their biggest nightmare is interrupting lunch/dinner. my favorite cinematic shots were the six aimlessly wandering in an empty street

Movie: Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb
Review: a satirical masterpiece. truly hilarious from start to finish. the fluoride in the water. the lack of fish in the war room buffet. “mein fuhrer I can walk.” the destruction of the coke vending machine. the b-52 pilot hero team. it was incredibly succinct. no fat whatsoever. love a 90 minute movie. the comedic timing of both the actors and the edits are hilarious. it made me burst out laughing multiple times. perfectly encapsulates the absurd mania of the Cold War and how really it’s just a bunch of idiots running the world.
